								<div class="title" id="post-title-1465480">
																		Producer&#039;s Commentary
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hornby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1259135); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1259135&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252378" alt="Hornby" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1259135)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hornby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1259135); return false;" >Hornby</a></span> <span class="odate time_1338436095 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 May 2012 03:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1465480">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Comments&nbsp;on&nbsp;production</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide&nbsp;production&nbsp;comments</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This project was created for an upper level university cinema and media studies course. Essentially, the course boiled down to spending a semester “designing, testing, and executing an in-depth, individual media project”. With near total free reign in terms of form and content, I elected to do an SCP-related audio drama following the rough conventions of a five act hour long television episode (a structure that actually dates back to the serials of the Golden Age of Radio). This is the reason for the act break and presence of spoken credits within the audio – a demand of the form. The final product came in a little short (just shy of 39 minutes rather than the usual 44), but since the time restriction was a self-imposed creative experiment, I chose not to shoehorn in additional content as filler). This project probably took between 125 and 175 hours to produce from start to finish.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Comments&nbsp;on&nbsp;content&nbsp;(includes&nbsp;several&nbsp;unmarked&nbsp;spoilers)</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide&nbsp;content&nbsp;comments</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>A couple of comments on the content worthy of explanation and disclaimer:</p>
<ul>
<li>It should be considered deliberately ambiguous whether the Overseer has informed the rest of the O5s about the incident, or whether he is acting without official approval. Headcanon it however you prefer.</li>
<li>A three person team is <em>not</em> enough to secure a major facility. As Hendricksen explains, Omega-4’s job is not to secure the station, but rather to gather intelligence about what went wrong so that sufficient forces can be allocated.</li>
<li>Physics does not work the way it is portrayed in the audio drama. That’s rather the point – I took artistic license for dramatic purposes.</li>
<li>I am aware that “Neptune Station” is not proper secure facility nomenclature. The formal name for the station is “Sector 23 Submarine Research Station for Project Daedalus”. “Neptune Station” is simply the informal shorthand.</li>
<li>At 4775 meters down, Neptune Station is technically deeper than is feasible with most modern technology, especially without creating a substantial positive pressure environment with an exotic gas atmosphere. I handwave this as the Foundation having sufficiently advanced resources to pull it off.</li>
<li>E-2157 is not the <a href="/scp-169">Leviathan</a>, but rather original to this tale. The Leviathan is, after a fashion, understood by the Foundation. E-2157 is not.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">A&nbsp;request:&nbsp;when&nbsp;discussing&nbsp;spoilers</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">please&nbsp;collapsible&nbsp;them.&nbsp;Thanks!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content"></div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<p>Advice: it’s worth listening past the end of the credits in Act V.</p>

							</div>

								
					
